This paper is about learning a Gaussian mixture model, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper presents an algorithm for properly learning a mixture of k Gaussians that is nearly optimal for any fixed k, and offers an agnostic learning guarantee. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper discusses sample and time complexity. The paper also mentions prior work on the topic, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
